snippet: Private exchanges, which oversee trading in private shares of Internet start-ups, will lose a lucrative client when Facebook holds its public offering.
abstract: Private exchanges, which oversee trading in private shares of Internet start-ups, will lose a lucrative client when Facebook holds its public offering.

byline.original: By EVELYN M. RUSLI and PETER LATTMAN

lead_paragraph: Not everyone on Wall Street is giddy over Facebook's initial public offering of stock.

headline.main: Losing a Goose That Laid the Golden Egg
